The <strong><code>min-width</code></strong> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS">CSS</a> property sets the minimum width of an element. It prevents the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/used_value">used value</a> of the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/width" title="The width CSS property sets an element's width. By default, it sets the width of the content area, but if box-sizing is set to border-box, it sets the width of the border area."><code>width</code></a> property from becoming smaller than the value specified for <code>min-width</code>.